OSCAR (Open Source Clinical Application Resource) - Installation

  Packages in oscar_mcmaster tar ball:
    [1] Java2 SDK Environment 
    [2] Jakarta Tomcat 
    [3] Mysql Database 
    [4] OSCAR source files
    [5] OSCAR web application files
    [6] OSCAR eDocument Repository
    [7] OSCAR Security Config file
    [8] OSCAR property files
    [9] Temporary SSL Keyfile
    [0] compat-libstdc++ rpm package
  
  
  Hardware Requirement
    [CPU] - Pentium 2 or higher (tested with Celeron 400)
    [MEM] - 128MB minumum, 256MB recommended (tested with 64MB)
    [HD ] - 600MB free space, 6 GB recommended 
    [CD ] - CD Rom Drive
    [NTW] - Networking capability 
    
  Software Requirement  
    [OS ] - Linux (tested with Redhat 7.2)
    [PKG] - Installation Type - Server
          - Developement Package selected (Gcc++ lib for JAVA)
          
  
  Quick Install from Scratch:
    
    REDHAT Installation:
    [1] Boot Linux Image from CD
    [2] Select Automatic Partition
    [3] Select "Server" Grade installation
    [4] Security Level : Medium, allow ssh
    [5] Add Development tools Package ("select individual package" option selected) 
    
    OSCAR Installation:
    [0] Login as root access
    
    [1] Untar the distribution in any directory
        tar zxvf oscar_mcmaster_x.x.tar.gz
    
    [2] Run install script in untar directory
        cd oscar_mcmaster
        ./install.sh
    
    [3] Add the following statement on /etc/profile file before the export statment
        
        JAVA_HOME="/usr/local/java"
	CATALINA_HOME="/usr/local/tomcat"
	PATH="$PATH:/usr/local/java/bin:/usr/local/tomcat/bin:/usr/local/mysql/bin"
	
	export JAVA_HOME CATALINA_HOME PATH USER LOGNAME MAIL HOSTNAME HISTSIZE INPUTRC

    [4] The oscar package should be installed. To start all serivces:
    
  +--------------------------------------------------------+
  | Starting up OSCAR:                                     |
  | [1]  cd /usr/local/mysql                               |
  | [2]  ./bin/safe_mysqld &                               |
  | [3]  cd /usr/local/tomcat/webapps/                     |
  | [4]  ../bin/startup.sh                                 |
  | [5]  open the client browser and run                   |
  |      https://<yourhostname>:8443/oscar_mcmaster/       |
  |                                                        |
  | You should see the oscar login page, then login as     |
  |                                                        |                                                     
  |                                                        |                                                     
  | OSCAR LOGIN |  USER ID   |  PASSWORD   |  PIN          |
  | Admin       | oscaradmin |  mac2002    |  1117         |
  | Doctor      | oscardoc   |  mac2002    |  1117         |
  | Receptionist| oscarrep   |  mac2002    |  1117         | 
  |                                                        |                                                     
  |                                                        |
  | Shutting down OSCAR:                                   |                                                     
  | [1] cd /usr/local/tomcat/webapps/                      |
  | [2] ../bin/shutdown.sh                                 |                                                     
  | [3] cd /usr/local/mysql                                |
  | [4] ../bin/mysqladmin -p<your_db_password> shutdown    |                                                     
  |                                                        |
  +--------------------------------------------------------+
        
        
    
    
    
    Installation notes:    
    
    If you like to change the database userid and password, you can do the following:
    
    Advanced MYSQL Configuration:
    [1] Starting mysql
        cd /usr/local/mysql
        ./bin/safe_mysqld & (if not starting up, please refer to http://www.mysql.com)
    [2] Configure the mysqladmin
        mysqladmin -u root password "<yourpassword>" please refer to the 
        oscar_mcmaster.properties file for database password
    [3] Grant permission to user
        mysql -u root -p<yourpassword> oscar_mcmaster
        mysql> grant all on oscar_mcmaster.* to root@localhost identified by "<yourpassword>"
    [4] Then try query on browser
        https://<yourhostname>:8443/oscar_mcmaster/mysql.jsp
        if you see "connection sucess!", you can access OSCAR
        
    Edit oscar_mcmaster.properties file
    [1] cd /root
    [2] vi oscar_mcmaster.properties file
    [3] change the value in db_username and db_password
    [4] save it
    [5] run oscar again

  